Preloadr

What the project is for
  Website preloader with loading image and transition effects integrated technique utilizing JavaScript image object caching, content preloading, critical CSS prioritizing and Paul Irish's classic Avoiding the FOUC v3.0 fix
Built with
  HTML/CSS/JavaScript
  loadCSS (optional extended browser support)
  Bootstrap 4 (optional example template)
How to configure and install it
  1. Add no-js class to html element
  2. Add critical CSS to head
  3. Preload external stylesheets ("rel" "as" and "onload" attributes)
  4. Add Avoiding the FOUC v3.0 fix script/styles to head
  5. Add loadCSS script to head
  6. Add .loading class to body
  7. Add #loader element to top of body
  8. Wrap content below #loader element in #wrapper element
  9. Link to preloadr.js
  10. Edit loading image source/dimensions in critical CSS and preloadr.js

An example of how to use it or get it running
  https://tightcode.github.io/preloadr
  Visit, reload the page or follow the first two links in the navbar

